sql:
SELECT sd.timestamp, sd.heart_rate
FROM sensor_data sd
WHERE sd.subject_id = '1' AND sd.heart_rate > 70;

SELECT AVG(heart_rate) AS average_heart_rate
FROM sensor_data
WHERE recording_id = '0';

SELECT AVG(heart_rate) AS average_heart_rate
FROM sensor_data
WHERE subject_id = '1' AND recording_id = '1';

external_knowledge:
Normal body temperature ranges from 36.5 to 37.5 degrees Celsius; A temperature above 37.5 is generally considered a slight fever; 
The World Health Organization defines 'normal' heart rates as between 60 and 100 beats per minute for adults; 
In this context, having an average heart rate above 70 might be considered a moderate level of intensity.
